This method intelligently manages document flow by attempting to insert specified newlines, but it includes robust internal logic to handle layout failures.

```python
def add_newline(self, number=1):
        """ Starts over again at the new line. If number is specified,
            it will leave multiple lines."""
        if isinstance(number, int):
            try:
                self.page._add_newline(self.font, number, self.double_spacing)
            except ValueError:
                self.add_page()
        else:
            raise TypeError("Number of newlines must be an integer.")
```

If the internal page layout fails to accommodate the requested newlines via a `ValueError`, it automatically moves to starting on a brand-new physical page.
